                    <msContents>
                        <summary>A woodblock printed Japanese translation by Kobayashi Yoshinao (1844-1905) of 'A compend of materia medica and therapeutics, for the use of students' (Philadelphia: Lippincott, 1869) by John Campbell Riley (1828-1879), and pubished in Tokyo by Shimamura Risuke in 1875.</summary>

                        <textLang mainLang="ja" source="IANA">Japanese</textLang>

                        <msItem n="1" xml:id="Japanese_87">

                            <author key="person_258450204" source="VIAF">
                                <persName type="original" xml:lang="ja"/>
                                <persName type="standard" xml:lang="en">John Campbell Riley</persName>
                                <note><p>Identified in the preface in Chinese characters, John
                                        Campbell Riley (1828-1879) was a Washington physician who in
                                        1859 became a professor at the National Medical College in
                                        Washington DC.</p></note>
                            </author>

                            <author>
                                <persName type="original" xml:lang="ja">>小林義直</persName>
                                <persName type="standard" xml:lang="ja-Latn">Kobayashi Yoshinao</persName>
                                <note>Kobayashi Yoshinao (1844-1905), was born in rural Fukuyama but
                                    in 1863 he went up to Edo (Tokyo), where he attended the Yōsho
                                    Shirabesho and Igakukan (the Bakufu institutions for the study
                                    of Western books and Western medicine, respectively) and also
                                    attended the private school of Tsuboi Hōshū. He subsequently
                                    returned to Fukuyama, where he taught English in the domain
                                    academy and was later instrumental in setting up a medical
                                    academy and hospital there. In 1872 he entered the Monbushō
                                    (Ministry of Education) and the following year was attached to
                                    the Translation Department with responsibility for medical
                                    books. In 1875, however, he left the Ministry to devote himself
                                    to translation and he subsequently produced a number of medical
                                    translations, either on his own or in collaboration with Tsuboi
                                    Hōshū and others; these included a manual of gynaecology, Kashi
                                    sanka tekiyō 華氏産科摘要 (1876), which was translated from an
                                    unidentified original.</note>
                            </author>

                            <respStmt>
                                <persName type="original" xml:lang="ja">島村利助</persName>
                                <persName type="standard" xml:lang="ja-Latn">Shimamura Risuke</persName>
                                <resp>Publisher</resp>
                                <note>A notice attached to the end of volume eight indicates that
                                    the publisher, Shimamura Risuke, was the official publisher of
                                    books for the Army Medical Corps, the Naval Hospital and the
                                    Medical Academy and that he specialized in medical books and
                                    translations; a catalogue of his publications attached to the
                                    end of the last volume includes a number of medical works as
                                    well as Saikoku risshihen, a translation of Samuel Smiles’
                                    Self-help. </note>
                            </respStmt>

                                <title type="original" xml:lang="ja" source="IANA">理礼氏薬物学</title>
                                <title type="standard" xml:lang="ja-Latn" source="IANA">Rireishi yakubutsugaku</title>
                                <title type="standard" xml:lang="en" source="IANA">Riley’s pharmacology</title>
                            

                            <note>方面に「（眉上「明治五壬申春刊行」）司馬盈之閲／小林義直訳（朱印「東京本郷弓町二丁目十三番地寄留小林義直版」）／理礼氏薬物学／明治八年十一月廿七日版権免許蘆灣漁舎梓」（蘆灣漁人は訳者の号）。刊記「東校官板御用所／軍医寮官板御用所／海軍病院官板御用所／発行書肆　英蘭堂　東京　島村利助」。巻末に「英蘭堂発兌書目録」（４丁）を附す。（印記）「医員小集会之記章」「医学社」。原書は「A compend of materia medica and therapeutics, for the use of students (Philadelphia: Lippincott, 1869)」、著者は John Campbell Riley (1828-1879)。</note>
                        </msItem>

